name: FDifferentialSetup6W
comment: Described which axles are powered by the engine. True == Powered.

properties.name: DifferentialConfig
properties.comment: Type of differential

methods.name: FindPeakTorque
methods.comment: Find the peak torque produced by the TorqueCurve

properties.name: TorqueCurve
properties.comment: Torque (Nm) at a given RPM

properties.name: MaxRPM
properties.comment: Maximum revolutions per minute of the engine

properties.name: MOI
properties.comment: Moment of inertia of the engine around the axis of rotation (Kgm^2).

properties.name: DampingRateFullThrottle
properties.comment: Damping rate of engine when full throttle is applied (Kgm^2/s)

properties.name: DampingRateZeroThrottleClutchEngaged
properties.comment: Damping rate of engine in at zero throttle when the clutch is engaged (Kgm^2/s)

properties.name: DampingRateZeroThrottleClutchDisengaged
properties.comment: Damping rate of engine in at zero throttle when the clutch is disengaged (in neutral gear) (Kgm^2/s)

properties.name: Ratio
properties.comment: Determines the amount of torque multiplication

properties.name: DownRatio
properties.comment: Value of engineRevs/maxEngineRevs that is low enough to gear down

properties.name: UpRatio
properties.comment: Value of engineRevs/maxEngineRevs that is high enough to gear up

properties.name: bUseGearAutoBox
properties.comment: Whether to use automatic transmission

properties.name: GearSwitchTime
properties.comment: Time it takes to switch gears (seconds)

properties.name: GearAutoBoxLatency
properties.comment: Minimum time it takes the automatic transmission to initiate a gear change (seconds)

properties.name: FinalRatio
properties.comment: The final gear ratio multiplies the transmission gear ratios.

properties.name: ForwardGears
properties.comment: Forward gear ratios (up to 30)

properties.name: ReverseGearRatio
properties.comment: Reverse gear ratio

properties.name: NeutralGearUpRatio
properties.comment: Value of engineRevs/maxEngineRevs that is high enough to increment gear

properties.name: ClutchStrength
properties.comment: Strength of clutch (Kgm^2/s)

methods.name: GenerateTireForces
methods.comment: Overridden so we can take advantage of camber

methods.comment: Overridden so we can take advantage of camber

methods.comment: Allocate and setup the PhysX vehicle

methods.name: GetLargestTireLoadValue
methods.comment: returns the current largest tire load of the vehicle

methods.name: GetLargestLateralSlip
methods.comment: returns the current largest lat slip of the vehicle

methods.name: GetLargestLongitudinalSlip
methods.comment: returns the current largest long slip of the vehicle

methods.name: GetHandbreakInput
methods.comment: Returns true if we have pulled the handbreak of the vehicle

properties.name: EngineSetup
properties.comment: Engine

properties.name: DifferentialSetup
properties.comment: Differential

properties.name: mUseDSOLGearbox
properties.comment: Use Jace's super awesome custom gearbox or not

properties.name: mDSOLMaxSlopeAngleLimit
properties.comment: Max slope Angle Limit (in degrees) in order to use all of SlopeShiftRatio

properties.name: mSlopeShiftRatio
properties.comment: Amount of ADDITIONAL required gear ratio in order to shift up or down, given a slope. The result is that on steep slopes, the vehicle will shift up at a higher ratio and shift down at a higher ratio.

properties.name: TransmissionSetup
properties.comment: Transmission data

properties.name: mDownShiftLatency
properties.comment: Multiplier for down shifting latency. Eg. it may be better to have a faster latency when downshifting

properties.name: SteeringCurve
properties.comment: Maximum steering versus forward speed (km/h)

properties.name: AckermannAccuracy
properties.comment: Accuracy of Ackermann steer calculation (range: 0..1)

properties.name: mAckermannData
properties.comment: The ackermann related settings.

properties.name: mFrontWheelMaxSteer
properties.comment:
Max front and rear steer angle that was set in the editor. These are needed as we mess with these values in the vehicle in-game
	    to achieve ackermann steering. These variables will preserve the initial values so we can use them in calculations.

properties.name: mMidAxleSeparation
properties.comment: width from front axle to mid axle

properties.name: mMidWidth
properties.comment: Width between mid wheels

properties.name: mDSOLDynGearboxData
properties.comment: Gearbox data that is tracked during simulation

properties.name: mDSOLSetupData
properties.comment: Gearbox setup data

properties.name: mPhysxUserData
properties.comment: Array of PhysX User defineable data that are passed to the shader

properties.name: mPhysxWheelUserData
properties.comment: Array of PhysXWheel User defineable data that are passed to the shader
